20be%20the%20strength-spotter%20for%20my%20children%2C%20just%20as%20my%20mom%20was%20for%20me.%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3EI%20always%20take%20pride%20in%20having%20learned%20how%20to%20parent%20from%20my%20own%20mom%20%E2%80%94%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ftwins-parenting-life-change-dad-experience-2026-5%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Ethe%20best%20example%3C%2Fa%3E.%20Not%20just%20from%20what%20she%20taught%20me%20to%20do%20with%20my%20kids%20once%20I%20had%20them%2C%20but%20also%20from%20the%20way%20she%20brought%20up%20my%20siblings%20and%20me.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EUnfortunately%2C%20she%20is%20no%20longer%20with%20us.%20But%20her%20countless%20memories%20keep%20me%20going%20and%20help%20guide%20my%20parenting%20every%20day.%20One%20of%20the%20best%20parenting%20hacks%20I%20learned%20from%20her%20was%20to%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fentrepreneurship-nature-vs-nurture-2010-3%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Enurture%20your%20child's%20strengths%3C%2Fa%3E%20from%20the%20start.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20have%20always%20enjoyed%20writing.%20stories%2C%20poems%2C%20recipes%2C%20letters%20%E2%80%94%20everything.%20In%20school%2C%20when%20we%20were%20assigned%20a%20simple%20five-line%20paragraph%2C%20I%20used%20to%20go%20past%20the%20word%20count%2C%20letting%20my%20creativity%20just%20spill%20out%20onto%20the%20paper.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMy%20mom%20was%20the%20first%20one%20to%20observe%20this%20talent.%20She%20used%20to%20tell%20me%20and%20everyone%20else%20that%20I%20was%20a%20gifted%20writer.%20She%20proudly%20showed%20my%20stories%20and%20poems%20to%20family%20and%20friends%2C%20and%20was%20always%20supportive%20of%20my%20reading%20habit%2C%20which%20helped%20hone%20my%20writing%20skills.%20To%20her%2C%20my%20writing%20was%20more%20than%20just%20a%20hobby.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EShe%20didn't%20just%20label%20me%20a%20writer%2C%20but%20even%20treated%20me%20like%20one.%20She%20read%20what%20I%20wrote%2C%20appreciated%20it%2C%20and%20made%20sure%20I%20f%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fwoman-with-older-parents-says-they-were-the-best-cheerleaders-2023-6%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Eelt%20that%20it%20mattered%3C%2Fa%3E.%20When%20one%20of%20my%20short%20stories%20got%20published%20in%20the%20local%20newspaper's%20kids%20section%2C%20she%20was%20over%20the%20moon.%20She%20made%20sure%20I%20got%20enough%20appreciation%20to%20keep%20nurturing%20this%20special%20skill.%20She%20knew%20something%20I%20didn't%20realize%20at%20the%20time.%20%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%225d1604aa-d5da-4937-b732-9dc8d3a45037%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EThings%20took%20a%20turn%20for%20the%20sake%20of%20practicality%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EI%20never%20really%20gave%20up%20writing.%20My%20diaries%20were%20packed%20with%20stories%2C%20poetry%2C%20and%20fanfiction.%20Writing%20was%20always%20there.%20But%20I%20never%20seriously%20considered%20it%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fstarted-freelancing-penny-a-word-never-gave-up-2025-4%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Eas%20a%20career.%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EDespite%20my%20love%20for%20words%2C%20when%20it%20came%20time%20to%20choose%20a%20major%2C%20I%20chose%20biology.%20I%20was%20good%20at%20science%2C%20and%20fields%20like%20genetics%20and%20microbiology%20felt%20like%20safe%20bets%20for%20a%20successful%20future.%20On%20paper%2C%20it%20was%20the%20logical%20choice.%20But%20logic%20doesn't%20always%20satisfy%20the%20soul.%20Even%20as%20I%20passed%20my%20exams%20with%20flying%20colors%2C%20I%20knew%20I%20never%20truly%20wanted%20to%20work%20in%20a%20lab.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%221004%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22The%20author%3Bs%20son%20models%20a%20sporting%20award%20he%20received.%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F69fcd431e1443b8dc48e2eab%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221157%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EThe%20author%20said%20she%20felt%20the%20need%20to%20pursue%20a%20career%20in%20a%20lucrative%20field%2C%20such%20as%20biology%2C%20when%20she%20was%20younger.%20Now%20she's%20helping%20her%20son%20chase%20his%20sports%20dreams.%3Cp%3ECourtesy%20of%20Ariba%20Mobin.%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EI%20married%20right%20after%20graduating%20and%20planned%20to%20take%20a%20year%20off%20to%20settle%20into%20my%20new%20life.%20When%20I%20had%20my%20first%20baby%2C%20my%20perspective%20shifted.%20I%20realized%20I%20didn't%20want%20to%20leave%20my%20child%20in%20day%20care%20while%20I%20did%20the%209-to-5%20grind%20in%20a%20field%20I%20wasn't%20really%20passionate%20about.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22efc193d1-2df2-4633-a565-0da30755c4f8%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EThat%20feeling%20of%20having%20potential%20in%20my%20words%20came%20back%20with%20full%20force%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EBy%20this%20time%2C%20my%20mom%20had%20spent%20twenty%20years%20telling%20me%20I%20was%20a%20writer.%20And%20when%20I%20needed%20work%20that%20aligned%20with%20my%20values%20as%20a%20parent%2C%20I%20decided%20to%20trust%20her%20label.%20%3Cbr%3E%3Cbr%3EI%20tried%20freelance%20writing%2C%20not%20entirely%20sure%20where%20it%20would%20lead.%20To%20my%20surprise%2C%20I%20thrived.%20Working%20from%20home%20while%20being%20there%20for%20my%20baby%20was%20exactly%20what%20I%20needed.%20%3Cbr%3E%3Cbr%3EA%20decade%20later%2C%20I%20have%20built%20a%20career%20as%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhow-turned-copywriting-side-hustle-into-974000-business-teacher-2022-12%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Econtent%20specialist%20and%20copywriter%3C%2Fa%3E.%20The%20science%20professional%20path%20is%20long%20gone%2C%20but%20that's%20for%20the%20better.%20It%20has%20been%20replaced%20by%20the%20career%20my%20mother%20saw%20for%20me%20before%20I%20could%20see%20it%20for%20myself.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%225f76248a-6616-4ccc-9b1e-39d66d6caedf%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EThe%20time%20came%20to%20carry%20the%20legacy%20forward%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3ENow%2C%20I%20have%20three%20children%20of%20my%20own%2C%20each%20with%20unique%20capabilities%2C%20and%20I%20have%20made%20it%20my%20mission%20to%20be%20their%20strength-spotter%2C%20just%20like%20my%20mom%20was%20for%20me.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMy%20eldest%20son%20has%20an%20incredible%20interest%20in%20sports%20and%20an%20impressive%20level%20of%20emotional%20control.%20Whenever%20he%20has%20a%20tough%20game%20day%2C%20I%20remind%20him%20that%20his%20discipline%20and%20calm%20head%20are%20the%20typical%20qualities%20of%20a%20great%20athlete.%20%3Cbr%3E%3Cbr%3EOn%20the%20contrary%2C%20my%20second%20son%20is%20a%20natural%20negotiator%20with%20mental%20math%20skills%20that%20are%20even%20better%20than%20adults.%20I%20tell%20him%20his%20ability%20to%20convince%20people%20and%20manage%20numbers%20will%20make%20him%20a%20fantastic%20entrepreneur%20one%20day.%3Cbr%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%22373%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22The%20author's%20daughter%20working%20on%20a%20craft%20project.%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F69fcd5fac9dd4cb81cda838f%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22533%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EThe%20author%20said%20her%20youngest%20child%20is%20creative%2C%20and%20she%20hopes%20to%20nurture%20and%20encourage%20that%20side%20of%20her.%3Cp%3ECourtesy%20of%20Ariba%20Mobin.%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EMy%20daughter%2C%20who%20isn't%20even%205%20yet%2C%20is%20already%20great%20at%20storytelling%2C%20organizing%2C%20and%20crafting.%20When%20she%20proudly%20shows%20me%20her%20little%20creations%2C%20I%20make%20sure%20she%20knows%20she%20has%20a%20creative%20eye.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EEven%20with%20unique%20capabilities%2C%20every%20child%20has%20flaws%2C%20too.%20My%20eldest%20son%20shows%20almost%20no%20interest%20in%20creative%20writing%2C%20and%20my%20second%20son%20is%20far%20from%20organized%2C%20which%20can%20be%20frustrating%20at%20times.%20But%20I%20always%20try%20to%20focus%20on%20wh