in-dropped-donald-trump-realizing-crook-brother-says-2023-3%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3EJeffrey%20Epstein's%20brother%3C%2Fa%3E%20saw%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fepstein-suicide-note-cellmate-nicholas-tartaglione-murder-2026-5%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Epurported%20suicide%20note%3C%2Fa%3E%20left%20by%20the%20now-dead%20financier%2C%20he%20didn't%20believe%20it%20was%20real.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMark%20Epstein%2C%20who%20has%20long%20maintained%20that%20his%20brother%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fjeffrey-epstein-brother-thinks-killed-jail-doj-report-2023-6%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Ewas%20murdered%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20told%20Business%20Insider%20the%20note%2C%20which%20was%20unsealed%20by%20a%20judge%20this%20week%2C%20is%20a%20forgery.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIt%20wouldn't%20be%20hard%20to%20get%20some%20pro%20forger%20to%20forge%20a%20note%2C%26quot%3B%20Mark%20Epstein%20told%20BI.%20%26quot%3BThat's%20the%20easiest%20fucking%20thing%20in%20the%20world%20to%20do.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fjeffrey-epstein-files-playbook-landing-billionaire-clients-mort-zuckerman-2026-3%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3EJeffrey%20Epstein%3C%2Fa%3E%20left%20the%20note%20in%20a%20Manhattan%20jail%20cell%20after%20a%20suicide%20attempt%2C%20according%20to%20Nicholas%20Tartaglione%2C%20his%20former%20cellmate%2C%20who%20claims%20to%20have%20found%20it.%20The%20note%20surfaced%20on%20Wednesday%20through%20a%20convoluted%20series%20of%20events.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20note%20was%20not%20written%20immediately%20before%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fjeffrey-epstein-death-autopsy-doctor-explains-delayed-suicide-ruling-2026-3%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3EEpstein's%20death%3C%2Fa%3E%20on%20August%2010%2C%202019%2C%20but%20during%20an%20earlier%20suicide%20attempt%20that%20July%2C%20according%20to%20Tartaglione.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ETartaglione%20%E2%80%94%20a%20former%20police%20officer%20who%20kidnapped%20and%20killed%20four%20people%20before%20burying%20them%20on%20his%20upstate%20New%20York%20property%20%E2%80%94%20said%20Epstein%20left%20the%20note%20in%20a%20book%20when%20he%20was%20transferred%20to%20a%20different%20cell%20following%20the%20July%2023%20suicide%20attempt%2C%20while%20he%20was%20awaiting%20trial%20on%20sex-trafficking%20charges.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ETartaglione's%20lawyers%20entered%20the%20note%20into%20his%20criminal%20case%2C%20where%20it%20was%20sealed%20in%20a%20dispute%20over%20his%20legal%20representation.%20US%20District%20Judge%20Kenneth%20Karas%2C%20who%20presided%20over%20the%20case%2C%20unsealed%20it%20this%20week%2C%20nearly%20six%20years%20after%20Tartaglione%20says%20he%20found%20it.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%22889%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22jeffrey%20epstein%20suicide%20note%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F69fe3772c9dd4cb81cda8af6%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22709%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EA%20purported%20suicide%20note%20from%20Jeffrey%20Epstein%20was%20unsealed%20this%20week.%3Cp%3EUS%20District%20Court%20for%20the%20Southern%20District%20of%20New%20York%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThey%20investigated%20me%20for%20month%20%E2%80%94%20FOUND%20NOTHING!!!%26quot%3B%20the%20note%20reads.%20%26quot%3BSo%2015%20year%20old%20charges%20resulted.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIt%20is%20a%20treat%20to%20be%20able%20to%20choose%20one's%20time%20to%20say%20goodbye%2C%26quot%3B%20it%20continues.%20%26quot%3BWatcha%20want%20me%20to%20do%20%E2%80%94%20Bust%20out%20cryin!!%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EJeffrey%20Epstein%20has%20used%20variations%20of%20the%20last%20line%20%E2%80%94%20%26quot%3BWatcha%20want%20me%20to%20do%20%E2%80%94%20Bust%20out%20cryin!!%26quot%3B%20%E2%80%94%20in%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.justice.gov%2Fepstein%2Ffiles%2FDataSet%25209%2FEFTA00818124.pdf%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eemails%3C%2Fa%3E%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.justice.gov%2Fepstein%2Ffiles%2FDataSet%25209%2FEFTA01031416.pdf%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eto%20Mark%20Epstein%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.justice.gov%2Fepstein%2Ffiles%2FDataSet%252011%2FEFTA02665629.pdf%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Efriends%3C%2Fa%3E%20that%20were%20made%20public%20by%20the%20Justice%20Department.%20It%20appears%20to%20be%20a%20reference%20to%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fyoutu.be%2FEU8LQd-wKhg%3Ft%3D812%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ethe%201931%20comedy%20video%20%26quot%3BLittle%20Daddy%26quot%3B%20from%20the%20show%20%26quot%3BLittle%20Rascals.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMark%20Epstein%20told%20Business%20Insider%20he%20does%20not%20recall%20those%20emails%2C%20but%20he%20would%20not%20be%20surprised%20if%20his%20brother%20referenced%20the%20show.%20He%20compared%20the%20show%20in%20the%201960s%20to%20%26quot%3BSpongeBob%20SquarePants%26quot%3B%20in%20its%20ubiquity.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWho%20didn't%20watch%20'The%20Little%20Rascals'%20in%20the%20'60s%20when%20we%20were%20kids%3F%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%20%26quot%3BI%20mean%2C%20everybody%20watched%20that.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMark%20Epstein%20said%20whoever%20forged%20the%20suicide%20note%20would%20have%20adopted%20his%20brother's%20%26quot%3Bvoice%26quot%3B%20from%20the%20emails%20included%20in%20the%20Epstein%20files%20%26quot%3Bto%20make%20it%20seem%20real.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIt's%20public%20knowledge%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%20%26quot%3BIt's%20in%20the%20emails.%20So%20they%20stole%20it%20from%20me%20to%20make%20it%20sound%20like%20it%20was%20him.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAccording%20to%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fstorage.courtlistener.com%2Frecap%2Fgov.uscourts.nysd.466714%2Fgov.uscourts.nysd.466714.613.0.pdf%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EKara's%20unsealing%20order%2C%20the%20note%3C%2Fa%3E%20was%20originally%20sealed%20in%20May%202021%20%E2%80%94%20well%20before%20Epstein's%20emails%20with%20the%20%26quot%3BLittle%20Rascals%26quot%3B%20reference%20became%20public%20earlier%20this%20year.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EA%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.justice.gov%2Fepstein%2Ffiles%2FDataSet%25208%2FEFTA00018224.pdf%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Etimeline%20included%20in%20the%20Epstein%20files%3C%2Fa%3E%20shows%20that%20it%20passed%20through%20the%20hands%20of%20multiple%20people%20who%20tried%20to%20authenticate%20it%20in%202019%20and%202020.%20Tartaglione%20also%20described%20the%20note%20in%20a%20podcast%20interview%20with%20the%20influencer%20Jessica%20Reed%20Kraus%20last%20year%2C%20also%20before%20the%20release%20of%20the%20Epstein%20files.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20note%20itself%20was%20not%20included%20in%20the%20Justice%20Department's%20Epstein%20files%2C%20nor%20in%20a%20128-page%20Justice%20Department%20inspector%20general%20report%20that%20followed%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fjejeffrey-epstein-death-justice-department-inspector-general-investigation-2023-3%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Efour%20years%20of%20investigation%20into%20Epstein's%20death%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EEpstein's%20first%20reported%20suicide%20attempt%20is%20itself%20a%20subject%20of%20dispute.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHe%20was%20found%20in%20his%20cell%20%26quot%3Bwith%20a%20homemade%20fashioned%20noose%20around%20his%20neck%2C%26quot%3B%20according%20to%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.justice.gov%2Fepstein%2Ffiles%2FDataSet%25209%2FEFTA00139603.pdf%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ean%20internal%20report%20from%20the%20Bureau%20of%20Prisons%3C%2Fa%3E.%20Tartaglione's%20lawyers%20said%20it%20was%20a%20suicide%20attempt.%20Epstein%20first%20told%20jail%20officials%20that%20Tartaglione%20tried%20to%20kill%20him%2C%20but%20a%20week%20later%20said%20he%20was%20%26quot%3Bextremely%20tired%26quot%3B%20the%20day%20of%20the%20incident%20and%20did%20not%20remember%20it%20well%2C%20according%20to%20a%20jail%20report.%20The%20inspector%20general's%20report%20ultimately%20characterized%20it%20as%20a%20first%20suicide%20attempt%20that%20preceded%20a%20successful%20one%20three%20weeks%20later.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMark%20Epstein%20said%20his%20brother%20recanted%20his%20claim%20that%20Tartaglione%20%26quot%3Broughed%20him%20up%26quot%3B%20because%20he%20did%20not%20want%20to%20be%20seen%20as%20a%20%26quot%3Bsnitch.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20reason%20he%20changed%20his%20tune%20is%20because%20he%20was%20afraid%20of%20retaliation%2C%26quot%3B%20Mark%20Epstein%20said.%20%26quot%3BIt's%20one%20thing%20to%20be%20a%20pedophile%20in%20prison.%20It's%20another%20thing%20to%20be%20a%20pedophile%20snitch%20in%20prison.%20That's%20no%20fun%20for%20anybody.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EKaras%20has%20indicated%20he%20would%20later%20unseal%20additional%20court%20documents%20related%20to%20the%20note%2C%20which%20could%20shed%20additional%20light%20on%20its%20authenticity.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMark%20Epstein%20remains%20skeptical.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI%20don't%20know%20if%20Tartaglione%20had%20this%20note.%20I%20doubt%20that.%20I%20doubt%20he%20found%20this%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%20%26quot%3BThere%20was%20no%20attempted%20suicide%2C%20so%20there%20was%20no%20suicide%20note.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHe%20says%20the%20most%20likely%20explanation%20of%20Jeffrey%20Epstein's%20death%20is%20that%20another%20person%20near%20his%20cell%2C%20out%20of%20view%20from%20cameras%2C%20killed%20him%2C%20and%20that%20the%20Justice%20Department%20is%20perpetuating%20a%20cover-up%20by%20not%20treating%20the%20death%20as%20a%20murder%20investigation.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMark%20Epstein%20said%20that%2C%20if%20his%20brother%20chose%20to%20kill%20himself%2C%20he%20wouldn't%20write%20a%20note%20at%20all.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIf%20he%20was%20going%20to%20commit%20suicide%2C%20he%20doesn't%20have%20to%20explain%20it%20to%20anybody%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fjeffrey-epstein-brother-says-suicide-note-forgery-little-rascals-2026-5%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1778273057000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F69fe38d6e1443b8dc48e364f%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fjeffrey-epstein-brother-says-suicide-note-forgery-little-rascals-2026-5%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Mark%20Epstein%20says%20the%20%26quot%3BLittle%20Rascals%26quot%3B%20reference%20in%20the%20note%20was%20copied%20from%20the%20Epstein%20files%20emails%20%E2%80%94%20but%20a%20judge%20says%20it%20was%20filed%20earlier.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22jshamsian%40businessinsider.com%20(Jacob%20Shamsian)%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A95%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Google%20Settles%20Racial%20Discrimination%20Lawsuit%20For%20%2450%20Million%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22The%20suit%20claimed%20the%20company%20steered%20them%20into%20lower-level%20and%20lower-paid%20jobs%20and%20subjected%20them%20to%20a%20hostile%20work%20environment%20if%20they%20speak%20out.%22%2C%22published%22%3A1778272487000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Fworld-news%2Fgoogle-settles-racial-discrimination-lawsuit-for-50-million-11469573%23publisher%3Dnewsstand%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22The%20suit%20claimed%20the%20company%20steered%20them%20into%20lower-level%20and%20lower-paid%20jobs%20and%20subjected%20them%20to%20a%20hostile%20work%20environment%20if%20they%20speak%20out.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A95%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Fworld-news%2Fgoogle-settles-racial-discrimination-lawsuit-for-50-million-11469573%23publisher%3Dnewsstand%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww-ndtv-com.cdn.ampproject.org%2Fc%2Fs%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Fworld-news%2Fgoogle-settles-racial-discrimination-lawsuit-for-50-million-11469573%2Famp%2F1%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Fworld-news%2Fgoogle-settles-racial-discrimination-lawsuit-for-50-million-11469573%2Famp%2F1%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22California%20babies%20are%20getting%20a%20free%20diaper%20stash%20at%20birth%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%226000%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22A%20woman%20changes%20a%20baby's%20diaper.%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F69fe3b6be1443b8dc48e3669%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%224000%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EGov.%20Gavin%20Newsom%20is%20praising%20the%20free%20diaper%20program%20as%20a%20way%20to%20lower%20costs%20for%20families.%3Cp%3EGalina%20Zhigalova%2FGetty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cul%3E%3Cli%3ECalifornia%20will%20give%20new%20parents%20400%20free%20diapers%20before%20they%20leave%20the%20hospital.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EGov.%20Gavin%20Newsom%20announced%20a%20first-in-the-nation%20diaper%20program%20launching%20this%20summer.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EThe%20state%20says%20it's%20part%20of%20a%20broader%20push%20to%20help%20ease%20the%20cost%20of%20early%20parenting.%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3ESome%20California%20hospitals%20are%20about%20to%20hand%20new%20parents%20a%20new%20state-sponsored%20freebie%3A%20roughly%20a%20month's%20worth%20of%20diapers.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fgavin-newsom-career-timeline%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3EGov.%20Gavin%20Newsom%3C%2Fa%3E%20on%20Friday%20announced%20what%20he%20called%20a%20first-in-the-nation%2C%20statewide%20program%20that%20will%20give%20families%20400%20free%20diapers%20before%20they%20leave%20the%20hospital%20after%20giving%20birth.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20program%20starts%20this%20summer.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20initiative%2C%20called%20%26quot%3BGolden%20State%20Start%2C%26quot%3B%20will%20launch%20at%20roughly%2065%20to%2075%20California%20hospitals%20in%20its%20first%20year%2C%20the%20governor's%20office%20said.%20The%20state%20said%20those%20hospitals%20account%20for%20about%20a%20quarter%20of%20California%20births.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20first%20wave%20of%20hospitals%20primarily%20serves%20low-income%20families%2C%20though%20state%20officials%20plan%20to%20expand%20the%20program%20statewide.%20Newsom's%20office%20did%20not%20say%20how%20many%20hospitals%20will%20eventually%20participate.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ECalifornia%20set%20aside%20%247.4%20million%20in%20its%202025%20budget%20to%20pay%20for%20the%20program%2C%20according%20to%20the%20AP.%20Newsom's%20latest%20budget%20proposal%20includes%20another%20%2412.5%20million%20to%20keep%20it%20funded%20through%20June%202027.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20a%20post%20on%20X%2C%20the%20governor%20described%20the%20initiative%20as%20part%20of%20a%20broader%20effort%20to%20ease%20the%20cost%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fevery-state-ranked-by-housing-cost-burden-2026%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Eburden%20on%20California%20families%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%20data-script%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fplatform.twitter.com%2Fwidgets.js%5C%22%20data-styles%3D%5C%22default-width%5C%22%20data-embed-type%3D%5C%22custom%5C%22%20data-type%3D%5C%22embed%5C%22%3E%3Cblockquote%20class%3D%5C%22twitter-tweet%5C%22%3E%3Cp%20lang%3D%5C%22en%5C%22%20dir%3D%5C%22ltr%5C%22%3EHUGE%20NEWS%3A%20California%20just%20became%20the%20FIRST%20state%20in%20America%20to%20provide%20FREE%20DIAPERS%20to%20all%20new%20parents.%3Cbr%3E%3Cbr%3ELaunching%20this%20summer.%3Cbr%3E%3Cbr%3ESince%20I%20became%20Governor%2C%20we%20have%20made%20preschool%20FREE%2C%20school%20meals%20FREE%2C%20and%20expanded%20paid%20family%20leave.%3Cbr%3E%3Cbr%3EStop%20talking%20about%20lowering%20costs%20for%E2%80%A6%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ft.co%2F2x919TdH24%5C%22%3Epic.twitter.com%2F2x919TdH24%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%E2%80%94%20Gavin%20Newsom%20(%40GavinNewsom)%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftwitter.com%2FGavinNewsom%2Fstatus%2F2052821127966470467%3Fref_src%3Dtwsrc%255Etfw%5C%22%3EMay%208%2C%202026%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fblockquote%3E%20%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3Cp%3ECalifornia%20partnered%20with%20nonprofit%20Baby2Baby%20to%20manufacture%20the%20diapers%2C%20which%20hospitals%20will%20distribute%20directly%20to%20families.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EDiapers%20are%20a%20major%20recurring%20expense%20for%20new%20parents%2C%20with%20families%20often%20spending%20hundreds%20or%20thousands%20of%20dollars%20annually%20during%20a%20child's%20first%20years.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20CDC%20recommends%20changing%20a%20newborn's%20diaper%20eight%20to%2012%20times%20a%20day%2C%20meaning%20California's%20400-diaper%20giveaway%20will%20likely%20last%20families%20about%20a%20month.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ENewsom%20said%20the%20program%20is%20also%20part%20of%20the%20state's%20broader%20push%20to%20lower%20the%20cost%20of%20early%20parenting.%20In%20the%20press%20release%2C%20he%20also%20highlighted%20recent%20rollouts%20for%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ffree-school-lunch-california-student-meals-budget-surplus-first-state-2021-7%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Efree%20school%20meals%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20free%20preschool%2C%20and%20extended%20after-school%20programs.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BCalifornia%20is%20taking%20on%20the%20cost%20of%20raising%20a%20family%20head-on%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said%20in%20a%20statement.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fcalifornia-babies-free-diapers-gavin-newsom-2026-5%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1778272279000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F69fe3bb6e1443b8dc48e366a%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fcalifornia-babies-free-diapers-gavin-newsom-2026-5%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22California%20will%20give%20new%20parents%20400%20free%20diapers%20at%20select%20hospitals%20under%